Responsibilities:
- Create test suites to identify bugs;
- Perform regression testing;
- Report issues and follow them until their closing state;
- Design, develop, execute and maintain test cases meeting business requirements;
- Identify actual or potential problems of the software at different states of the development;
- Work closely and communicate effectively with development and other teams to understand the features and create comprehensive test plans to verify functionality;
- Collaborate with team members to improve testing processes;
- Participation in backlog grooming and retro.
Requirements:
- 3+ years of QA experience;
- Experience in testing and debugging mobile applications: difference between platforms, testing approaches and techniques etc.;
- Experience of work in Agile environment;
- Able to design, develop, execute and maintain test cases and other test documentation;
- Able to use the Testing Tools, Dev console, Postman, etc.;
- Experience in Bug tracking tools (Jira, Trello, etc.);
- Provide comprehensive, clear test reports;
- Experience with API testing tools (Insomnia, Postman) sniffer tools, (Fiddler, Charles)
- Basic SQL knowledge
- Good communication skills to interact with local/remote teams effectively.<b>Skills</b>:        Regression Testing,                     Postman,                     Jira,                     Trello,                     API Testing,                     Fiddler,                     QA Software &amp; Testing Tools,                     SQL

